Sequence Information.Peptide Name: CATH_BRALE (cathelicidin; Gly-rich, natural AMPs; ancient fish,  animals)

Literature Information.Literature: Activity: active against two Gram-negative fish pathogens A. salmonicida and A. hydrophila (MIC 9.4 uM) as well as P. aeruginosa IS 1411 (MIC 1.17 uM), P. aeruginosa ATCC 27853 (MIC 4.7 uM), E. coli ATCC 25922 (MIC 2.34 uM), E. coli IS 1342 (MIC 4.7 uM), K. pneumoniae IS 1373 (18.8 uM), A. baumannii (MIC 4.7 uM), P. mirabilis (MIC 18 uM), A. sobria (MIC 18.8 uM), Gram-positive S. aureus ATCC 2592 (MIC 11-45 uM), E. faecium (MIC 11.4 uM), and fungi S. mould (11-22 uM), C. albicans ATCC 2002 (MIC 2.3 uM), and C. glabrata IS 0902 (MIC 9.4 uM).
Literature Information.Author: Li Z, Zhang S, Gao J, Guang H, Tian Y, Zhao Z, Wang Y, Yu H.2013
Literature Information.Title: Structural and functional characterization of CATH_BRALE, the defense molecule in the ancient salmonoid, Brachymystax lenok
